67// bn_div_words divides a double-width |h|,|l| by |d| and returns the result,
68// which must fit in a |BN_ULONG|.
69OPENSSL_UNUSED static BN_ULONG bn_div_words(BN_ULONG h, BN_ULONG l,
70 BN_ULONG d) {
71 BN_ULONG dh, dl, q, ret = 0, th, tl, t;
72 int i, count = 2;
73
74 if (d == 0) {
75 return BN_MASK2;
76 }
77
78 i = BN_num_bits_word(d);
79 assert((i == BN_BITS2) || (h <= (BN_ULONG)1 << i));
80
81 i = BN_BITS2 - i;
82 if (h >= d) {
83 h -= d;
84 }
85
86 if (i) {
87 d <<= i;
88 h = (h << i) | (l >> (BN_BITS2 - i));
89 l <<= i;
90 }
91 dh = (d & BN_MASK2h) >> BN_BITS4;
92 dl = (d & BN_MASK2l);
93 for (;;) {
94 if ((h >> BN_BITS4) == dh) {
95 q = BN_MASK2l;
96 } else {
97 q = h / dh;
98 }
99
100 th = q * dh;
101 tl = dl * q;
102 for (;;) {
103 t = h - th;
104 if ((t & BN_MASK2h) ||
105 ((tl) <= ((t << BN_BITS4) | ((l & BN_MASK2h) >> BN_BITS4)))) {
106 break;
107 }
108 q--;
109 th -= dh;
110 tl -= dl;
111 }
112 t = (tl >> BN_BITS4);
113 tl = (tl << BN_BITS4) & BN_MASK2h;
114 th += t;
115
116 if (l < tl) {
117 th++;
118 }
119 l -= tl;
120 if (h < th) {
121 h += d;
122 q--;
123 }
124 h -= th;
125
126 if (--count == 0) {
127 break;
128 }
129
130 ret = q << BN_BITS4;
131 h = (h << BN_BITS4) | (l >> BN_BITS4);
132 l = (l & BN_MASK2l) << BN_BITS4;
133 }
134
135 ret |= q;
136 return ret;
137}

139static inline void bn_div_rem_words(BN_ULONG *quotient_out, BN_ULONG *rem_out,
140 BN_ULONG n0, BN_ULONG n1, BN_ULONG d0) {
141 // GCC and Clang generate function calls to |__udivdi3| and |__umoddi3| when
142 // the |BN_ULLONG|-based C code is used.
143 //
144 // GCC bugs:
145 // * https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=14224
146 // * https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=43721
147 // * https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=54183
148 // * https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=58897
149 // * https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=65668
150 //
151 // Clang bugs:
152 // * https://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=6397
153 // * https://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=12418
154 //
155 // These issues aren't specific to x86 and x86_64, so it might be worthwhile
156 // to add more assembly language implementations.
157#if defined(BN_CAN_USE_INLINE_ASM) && defined(OPENSSL_X86)
158 __asm__ volatile("divl %4"
159 : "=a"(*quotient_out), "=d"(*rem_out)
160 : "a"(n1), "d"(n0), "rm"(d0)
161 : "cc");
162#elif defined(BN_CAN_USE_INLINE_ASM) && defined(OPENSSL_X86_64)
163 __asm__ volatile("divq %4"
164 : "=a"(*quotient_out), "=d"(*rem_out)
165 : "a"(n1), "d"(n0), "rm"(d0)
166 : "cc");
167#else
168#if defined(BN_CAN_DIVIDE_ULLONG)
169 BN_ULLONG n = (((BN_ULLONG)n0) << BN_BITS2) | n1;
170 *quotient_out = (BN_ULONG)(n / d0);
171#else
172 *quotient_out = bn_div_words(n0, n1, d0);
173#endif
174 *rem_out = n1 - (*quotient_out * d0);
175#endif
176}
177
178// BN_div computes "quotient := numerator / divisor", rounding towards zero,
179// and sets up |rem| such that "quotient * divisor + rem = numerator" holds.
180//
181// Thus:
182//
183// quotient->neg == numerator->neg ^ divisor->neg
184// (unless the result is zero)
185// rem->neg == numerator->neg
186// (unless the remainder is zero)
187//
188// If |quotient| or |rem| is NULL, the respective value is not returned.
189//
190// This was specifically designed to contain fewer branches that may leak
191// sensitive information; see "New Branch Prediction Vulnerabilities in OpenSSL
192// and Necessary Software Countermeasures" by Onur Acıçmez, Shay Gueron, and
193// Jean-Pierre Seifert.
194int BN_div(BIGNUM *quotient, BIGNUM *rem, const BIGNUM *numerator,
195 const BIGNUM *divisor, BN_CTX *ctx) {
196 int norm_shift, loop;
197 BIGNUM wnum;
198 BN_ULONG *resp, *wnump;
199 BN_ULONG d0, d1;
200 int num_n, div_n;
201
202 // This function relies on the historical minimal-width |BIGNUM| invariant.
203 // It is already not constant-time (constant-time reductions should use
204 // Montgomery logic), so we shrink all inputs and intermediate values to
205 // retain the previous behavior.
206
207 // Invalid zero-padding would have particularly bad consequences.
208 int numerator_width = bn_minimal_width(numerator);
209 int divisor_width = bn_minimal_width(divisor);
210 if ((numerator_width > 0 && numerator->d[numerator_width - 1] == 0) ||
211 (divisor_width > 0 && divisor->d[divisor_width - 1] == 0)) {
212 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(BN, BN_R_NOT_INITIALIZED);
213 return 0;
214 }
215
216 if (BN_is_zero(divisor)) {
217 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(BN, BN_R_DIV_BY_ZERO);
218 return 0;
219 }
220
221 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
222 BIGNUM *tmp = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
223 BIGNUM *snum = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
224 BIGNUM *sdiv = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
225 BIGNUM *res = NULL;
226 if (quotient == NULL) {
227 res = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
228 } else {
229 res = quotient;
230 }
231 if (sdiv == NULL || res == NULL) {
232 goto err;
233 }
234
235 // First we normalise the numbers
236 norm_shift = BN_BITS2 - (BN_num_bits(divisor) % BN_BITS2);
237 if (!BN_lshift(sdiv, divisor, norm_shift)) {
238 goto err;
239 }
240 bn_set_minimal_width(sdiv);
241 sdiv->neg = 0;
242 norm_shift += BN_BITS2;
243 if (!BN_lshift(snum, numerator, norm_shift)) {
244 goto err;
245 }
246 bn_set_minimal_width(snum);
247 snum->neg = 0;
248
249 // Since we don't want to have special-case logic for the case where snum is
250 // larger than sdiv, we pad snum with enough zeroes without changing its
251 // value.
252 if (snum->width <= sdiv->width + 1) {
253 if (!bn_wexpand(snum, sdiv->width + 2)) {
254 goto err;
255 }
256 for (int i = snum->width; i < sdiv->width + 2; i++) {
257 snum->d[i] = 0;
258 }
259 snum->width = sdiv->width + 2;
260 } else {
261 if (!bn_wexpand(snum, snum->width + 1)) {
262 goto err;
263 }
264 snum->d[snum->width] = 0;
265 snum->width++;
266 }
267
268 div_n = sdiv->width;
269 num_n = snum->width;
270 loop = num_n - div_n;
271 // Lets setup a 'window' into snum
272 // This is the part that corresponds to the current
273 // 'area' being divided
274 wnum.neg = 0;
275 wnum.d = &(snum->d[loop]);
276 wnum.width = div_n;
277 // only needed when BN_ucmp messes up the values between width and max
278 wnum.dmax = snum->dmax - loop; // so we don't step out of bounds
279
280 // Get the top 2 words of sdiv
281 // div_n=sdiv->width;
282 d0 = sdiv->d[div_n - 1];
283 d1 = (div_n == 1) ? 0 : sdiv->d[div_n - 2];
284
285 // pointer to the 'top' of snum
286 wnump = &(snum->d[num_n - 1]);
287
288 // Setup to 'res'
289 res->neg = (numerator->neg ^ divisor->neg);
290 if (!bn_wexpand(res, loop + 1)) {
291 goto err;
292 }
293 res->width = loop - 1;
294 resp = &(res->d[loop - 1]);
295
296 // space for temp
297 if (!bn_wexpand(tmp, div_n + 1)) {
298 goto err;
299 }
300
301 // if res->width == 0 then clear the neg value otherwise decrease
302 // the resp pointer
303 if (res->width == 0) {
304 res->neg = 0;
305 } else {
306 resp--;
307 }
308
309 for (int i = 0; i < loop - 1; i++, wnump--, resp--) {
310 BN_ULONG q, l0;
311 // the first part of the loop uses the top two words of snum and sdiv to
312 // calculate a BN_ULONG q such that | wnum - sdiv * q | < sdiv
313 BN_ULONG n0, n1, rm = 0;
314
315 n0 = wnump[0];
316 n1 = wnump[-1];
317 if (n0 == d0) {
318 q = BN_MASK2;
319 } else {
320 // n0 < d0
321 bn_div_rem_words(&q, &rm, n0, n1, d0);
322
323#ifdef BN_ULLONG
324 BN_ULLONG t2 = (BN_ULLONG)d1 * q;
325 for (;;) {
326 if (t2 <= ((((BN_ULLONG)rm) << BN_BITS2) | wnump[-2])) {
327 break;
328 }
329 q--;
330 rm += d0;
331 if (rm < d0) {
332 break; // don't let rm overflow
333 }
334 t2 -= d1;
335 }
336#else // !BN_ULLONG
337 BN_ULONG t2l, t2h;
338 BN_UMULT_LOHI(t2l, t2h, d1, q);
339 for (;;) {
340 if (t2h < rm ||
341 (t2h == rm && t2l <= wnump[-2])) {
342 break;
343 }
344 q--;
345 rm += d0;
346 if (rm < d0) {
347 break; // don't let rm overflow
348 }
349 if (t2l < d1) {
350 t2h--;
351 }
352 t2l -= d1;
353 }
354#endif // !BN_ULLONG
355 }
356
357 l0 = bn_mul_words(tmp->d, sdiv->d, div_n, q);
358 tmp->d[div_n] = l0;
359 wnum.d--;
360 // ingore top values of the bignums just sub the two
361 // BN_ULONG arrays with bn_sub_words
362 if (bn_sub_words(wnum.d, wnum.d, tmp->d, div_n + 1)) {
363 // Note: As we have considered only the leading
364 // two BN_ULONGs in the calculation of q, sdiv * q
365 // might be greater than wnum (but then (q-1) * sdiv
366 // is less or equal than wnum)
367 q--;
368 if (bn_add_words(wnum.d, wnum.d, sdiv->d, div_n)) {
369 // we can't have an overflow here (assuming
370 // that q != 0, but if q == 0 then tmp is
371 // zero anyway)
372 (*wnump)++;
373 }
374 }
375 // store part of the result
376 *resp = q;
377 }
378
379 bn_set_minimal_width(snum);
380
381 if (rem != NULL) {
382 // Keep a copy of the neg flag in numerator because if |rem| == |numerator|
383 // |BN_rshift| will overwrite it.
384 int neg = numerator->neg;
385 if (!BN_rshift(rem, snum, norm_shift)) {
386 goto err;
387 }
388 if (!BN_is_zero(rem)) {
389 rem->neg = neg;
390 }
391 }
392
393 bn_set_minimal_width(res);
394 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
395 return 1;
396
397err:
398 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
399 return 0;
400}
401
402int BN_nnmod(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *m, const BIGNUM *d, BN_CTX *ctx) {
403 if (!(BN_mod(r, m, d, ctx))) {
404 return 0;
405 }
406 if (!r->neg) {
407 return 1;
408 }
409
410 // now -|d| < r < 0, so we have to set r := r + |d|.
411 return (d->neg ? BN_sub : BN_add)(r, r, d);
412}
413
414BN_ULONG bn_reduce_once(BN_ULONG *r, const BN_ULONG *a, BN_ULONG carry,
415 const BN_ULONG *m, size_t num) {
416 assert(r != a);
417 // |r| = |a| - |m|. |bn_sub_words| performs the bulk of the subtraction, and
418 // then we apply the borrow to |carry|.
419 carry -= bn_sub_words(r, a, m, num);
420 // We know 0 <= |a| < 2*|m|, so -|m| <= |r| < |m|.
421 //
422 // If 0 <= |r| < |m|, |r| fits in |num| words and |carry| is zero. We then
423 // wish to select |r| as the answer. Otherwise -m <= r < 0 and we wish to
424 // return |r| + |m|, or |a|. |carry| must then be -1 or all ones. In both
425 // cases, |carry| is a suitable input to |bn_select_words|.
426 //
427 // Although |carry| may be one if it was one on input and |bn_sub_words|
428 // returns zero, this would give |r| > |m|, violating our input assumptions.
429 assert(carry == 0 || carry == (BN_ULONG)-1);
430 bn_select_words(r, carry, a /* r < 0 */, r /* r >= 0 */, num);
431 return carry;
432}
433
434BN_ULONG bn_reduce_once_in_place(BN_ULONG *r, BN_ULONG carry, const BN_ULONG *m,
435 BN_ULONG *tmp, size_t num) {
436 // See |bn_reduce_once| for why this logic works.
437 carry -= bn_sub_words(tmp, r, m, num);
438 assert(carry == 0 || carry == (BN_ULONG)-1);
439 bn_select_words(r, carry, r /* tmp < 0 */, tmp /* tmp >= 0 */, num);
440 return carry;
441}
442
443void bn_mod_sub_words(BN_ULONG *r, const BN_ULONG *a, const BN_ULONG *b,
444 const BN_ULONG *m, BN_ULONG *tmp, size_t num) {
445 // r = a - b
446 BN_ULONG borrow = bn_sub_words(r, a, b, num);
447 // tmp = a - b + m
448 bn_add_words(tmp, r, m, num);
449 bn_select_words(r, 0 - borrow, tmp /* r < 0 */, r /* r >= 0 */, num);
450}
451
452void bn_mod_add_words(BN_ULONG *r, const BN_ULONG *a, const BN_ULONG *b,
453 const BN_ULONG *m, BN_ULONG *tmp, size_t num) {
454 BN_ULONG carry = bn_add_words(r, a, b, num);
455 bn_reduce_once_in_place(r, carry, m, tmp, num);
456}

458int bn_div_consttime(BIGNUM *quotient, BIGNUM *remainder,
459 const BIGNUM *numerator, const BIGNUM *divisor,
460 BN_CTX *ctx) {
461 if (BN_is_negative(numerator) || BN_is_negative(divisor)) {
462 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(BN, BN_R_NEGATIVE_NUMBER);
463 return 0;
464 }
465 if (BN_is_zero(divisor)) {
466 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(BN, BN_R_DIV_BY_ZERO);
467 return 0;
468 }
469
470 // This function implements long division in binary. It is not very efficient,
471 // but it is simple, easy to make constant-time, and performant enough for RSA
472 // key generation.
473
474 int ret = 0;
475 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
476 BIGNUM *q = quotient, *r = remainder;
477 if (quotient == NULL || quotient == numerator || quotient == divisor) {
478 q = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
479 }
480 if (remainder == NULL || remainder == numerator || remainder == divisor) {
481 r = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
482 }
483 BIGNUM *tmp = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
484 if (q == NULL || r == NULL || tmp == NULL ||
485 !bn_wexpand(q, numerator->width) ||
486 !bn_wexpand(r, divisor->width) ||
487 !bn_wexpand(tmp, divisor->width)) {
488 goto err;
489 }
490
491 OPENSSL_memset(q->d, 0, numerator->width * sizeof(BN_ULONG));
492 q->width = numerator->width;
493 q->neg = 0;
494
495 OPENSSL_memset(r->d, 0, divisor->width * sizeof(BN_ULONG));
496 r->width = divisor->width;
497 r->neg = 0;
498
499 // Incorporate |numerator| into |r|, one bit at a time, reducing after each
500 // step. At the start of each loop iteration, |r| < |divisor|
501 for (int i = numerator->width - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
502 for (int bit = BN_BITS2 - 1; bit >= 0; bit--) {
503 // Incorporate the next bit of the numerator, by computing
504 // r = 2*r or 2*r + 1. Note the result fits in one more word. We store the
505 // extra word in |carry|.
506 BN_ULONG carry = bn_add_words(r->d, r->d, r->d, divisor->width);
507 r->d[0] |= (numerator->d[i] >> bit) & 1;
508 // |r| was previously fully-reduced, so we know:
509 // 2*0 <= r <= 2*(divisor-1) + 1
510 // 0 <= r <= 2*divisor - 1 < 2*divisor.
511 // Thus |r| satisfies the preconditions for |bn_reduce_once_in_place|.
512 BN_ULONG subtracted = bn_reduce_once_in_place(r->d, carry, divisor->d,
513 tmp->d, divisor->width);
514 // The corresponding bit of the quotient is set iff we needed to subtract.
515 q->d[i] |= (~subtracted & 1) << bit;
516 }
517 }
518
519 if ((quotient != NULL && !BN_copy(quotient, q)) ||
520 (remainder != NULL && !BN_copy(remainder, r))) {
521 goto err;
522 }
523
524 ret = 1;
525
526err:
527 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
528 return ret;
529}
530
531static BIGNUM *bn_scratch_space_from_ctx(size_t width, BN_CTX *ctx) {
532 BIGNUM *ret = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
533 if (ret == NULL ||
534 !bn_wexpand(ret, width)) {
535 return NULL;
536 }
537 ret->neg = 0;
538 ret->width = width;
539 return ret;
540}
541
542// bn_resized_from_ctx returns |bn| with width at least |width| or NULL on
543// error. This is so it may be used with low-level "words" functions. If
544// necessary, it allocates a new |BIGNUM| with a lifetime of the current scope
545// in |ctx|, so the caller does not need to explicitly free it. |bn| must fit in
546// |width| words.
547static const BIGNUM *bn_resized_from_ctx(const BIGNUM *bn, size_t width,
548 BN_CTX *ctx) {
549 if ((size_t)bn->width >= width) {
550 // Any excess words must be zero.
551 assert(bn_fits_in_words(bn, width));
552 return bn;
553 }
554 BIGNUM *ret = bn_scratch_space_from_ctx(width, ctx);
555 if (ret == NULL ||
556 !BN_copy(ret, bn) ||
557 !bn_resize_words(ret, width)) {
558 return NULL;
559 }
560 return ret;
561}

563int BN_mod_add(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b, const BIGNUM *m,
564 BN_CTX *ctx) {
565 if (!BN_add(r, a, b)) {
566 return 0;
567 }
568 return BN_nnmod(r, r, m, ctx);
569}
570
571int BN_mod_add_quick(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b,
572 const BIGNUM *m) {
573 BN_CTX *ctx = BN_CTX_new();
574 int ok = ctx != NULL &&
575 bn_mod_add_consttime(r, a, b, m, ctx);
576 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
577 return ok;
578}
579
580int bn_mod_add_consttime(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b,
581 const BIGNUM *m, BN_CTX *ctx) {
582 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
583 a = bn_resized_from_ctx(a, m->width, ctx);
584 b = bn_resized_from_ctx(b, m->width, ctx);
585 BIGNUM *tmp = bn_scratch_space_from_ctx(m->width, ctx);
586 int ok = a != NULL && b != NULL && tmp != NULL &&
587 bn_wexpand(r, m->width);
588 if (ok) {
589 bn_mod_add_words(r->d, a->d, b->d, m->d, tmp->d, m->width);
590 r->width = m->width;
591 r->neg = 0;
592 }
593 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
594 return ok;
595}

597int BN_mod_sub(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b, const BIGNUM *m,
598 BN_CTX *ctx) {
599 if (!BN_sub(r, a, b)) {
600 return 0;
601 }
602 return BN_nnmod(r, r, m, ctx);
603}
604
605int bn_mod_sub_consttime(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b,
606 const BIGNUM *m, BN_CTX *ctx) {
607 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
608 a = bn_resized_from_ctx(a, m->width, ctx);
609 b = bn_resized_from_ctx(b, m->width, ctx);
610 BIGNUM *tmp = bn_scratch_space_from_ctx(m->width, ctx);
611 int ok = a != NULL && b != NULL && tmp != NULL &&
612 bn_wexpand(r, m->width);
613 if (ok) {
614 bn_mod_sub_words(r->d, a->d, b->d, m->d, tmp->d, m->width);
615 r->width = m->width;
616 r->neg = 0;
617 }
618 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
619 return ok;
620}
621
622int BN_mod_sub_quick(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b,
623 const BIGNUM *m) {
624 BN_CTX *ctx = BN_CTX_new();
625 int ok = ctx != NULL &&
626 bn_mod_sub_consttime(r, a, b, m, ctx);
627 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
628 return ok;
629}
630
631int BN_mod_mul(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *b, const BIGNUM *m,
632 BN_CTX *ctx) {
633 BIGNUM *t;
634 int ret = 0;
635
636 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
637 t = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
638 if (t == NULL) {
639 goto err;
640 }
641
642 if (a == b) {
643 if (!BN_sqr(t, a, ctx)) {
644 goto err;
645 }
646 } else {
647 if (!BN_mul(t, a, b, ctx)) {
648 goto err;
649 }
650 }
651
652 if (!BN_nnmod(r, t, m, ctx)) {
653 goto err;
654 }
655
656 ret = 1;
657
658err:
659 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
660 return ret;
661}
662
663int BN_mod_sqr(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, const BIGNUM *m, BN_CTX *ctx) {
664 if (!BN_sqr(r, a, ctx)) {
665 return 0;
666 }
667
668 // r->neg == 0, thus we don't need BN_nnmod
669 return BN_mod(r, r, m, ctx);
670}

672int BN_mod_lshift(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, int n, const BIGNUM *m,
673 BN_CTX *ctx) {
674 BIGNUM *abs_m = NULL;
675 int ret;
676
677 if (!BN_nnmod(r, a, m, ctx)) {
678 return 0;
679 }
680
681 if (m->neg) {
682 abs_m = BN_dup(m);
683 if (abs_m == NULL) {
684 return 0;
685 }
686 abs_m->neg = 0;
687 }
688
689 ret = bn_mod_lshift_consttime(r, r, n, (abs_m ? abs_m : m), ctx);
690
691 BN_free(abs_m);
692 return ret;
693}

695int bn_mod_lshift_consttime(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, int n, const BIGNUM *m,
696 BN_CTX *ctx) {
697 if (!BN_copy(r, a)) {
698 return 0;
699 }
700 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
701 if (!bn_mod_lshift1_consttime(r, r, m, ctx)) {
702 return 0;
703 }
704 }
705 return 1;
706}

711 bn_mod_lshift_consttime(r, a, n, m, ctx);
712 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
713 return ok;
714}

737BN_ULONG BN_div_word(BIGNUM *a, BN_ULONG w) {
738 BN_ULONG ret = 0;
739 int i, j;
740
741 if (!w) {
742 // actually this an error (division by zero)
743 return (BN_ULONG) - 1;
744 }
745
746 if (a->width == 0) {
747 return 0;
748 }
749
750 // normalize input for |bn_div_rem_words|.
751 j = BN_BITS2 - BN_num_bits_word(w);
752 w <<= j;
753 if (!BN_lshift(a, a, j)) {
754 return (BN_ULONG) - 1;
755 }
756
757 for (i = a->width - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
758 BN_ULONG l = a->d[i];
759 BN_ULONG d;
760 BN_ULONG unused_rem;
761 bn_div_rem_words(&d, &unused_rem, ret, l, w);
762 ret = l - (d * w);
763 a->d[i] = d;
764 }
765
766 bn_set_minimal_width(a);
767 ret >>= j;
768 return ret;
769}
770
771BN_ULONG BN_mod_word(const BIGNUM *a, BN_ULONG w) {
772#ifndef BN_CAN_DIVIDE_ULLONG
773 BN_ULONG ret = 0;
774#else
775 BN_ULLONG ret = 0;
776#endif
777 int i;
778
779 if (w == 0) {
780 return (BN_ULONG) -1;
781 }
782
783#ifndef BN_CAN_DIVIDE_ULLONG
784 // If |w| is too long and we don't have |BN_ULLONG| division then we need to
785 // fall back to using |BN_div_word|.
786 if (w > ((BN_ULONG)1 << BN_BITS4)) {
787 BIGNUM *tmp = BN_dup(a);
788 if (tmp == NULL) {
789 return (BN_ULONG)-1;
790 }
791 ret = BN_div_word(tmp, w);
792 BN_free(tmp);
793 return ret;
794 }
795#endif
796
797 for (i = a->width - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
798#ifndef BN_CAN_DIVIDE_ULLONG
799 ret = ((ret << BN_BITS4) | ((a->d[i] >> BN_BITS4) & BN_MASK2l)) % w;
800 ret = ((ret << BN_BITS4) | (a->d[i] & BN_MASK2l)) % w;
801#else
802 ret = (BN_ULLONG)(((ret << (BN_ULLONG)BN_BITS2) | a->d[i]) % (BN_ULLONG)w);
803#endif
804 }
805 return (BN_ULONG)ret;
806}
807
808int BN_mod_pow2(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, size_t e) {
809 if (e == 0 || a->width == 0) {
810 BN_zero(r);
811 return 1;
812 }
813
814 size_t num_words = 1 + ((e - 1) / BN_BITS2);
815
816 // If |a| definitely has less than |e| bits, just BN_copy.
817 if ((size_t) a->width < num_words) {
818 return BN_copy(r, a) != NULL;
819 }
820
821 // Otherwise, first make sure we have enough space in |r|.
822 // Note that this will fail if num_words > INT_MAX.
823 if (!bn_wexpand(r, num_words)) {
824 return 0;
825 }
826
827 // Copy the content of |a| into |r|.
828 OPENSSL_memcpy(r->d, a->d, num_words * sizeof(BN_ULONG));
829
830 // If |e| isn't word-aligned, we have to mask off some of our bits.
831 size_t top_word_exponent = e % (sizeof(BN_ULONG) * 8);
832 if (top_word_exponent != 0) {
833 r->d[num_words - 1] &= (((BN_ULONG) 1) << top_word_exponent) - 1;
834 }
835
836 // Fill in the remaining fields of |r|.
837 r->neg = a->neg;
838 r->width = (int) num_words;
839 bn_set_minimal_width(r);
840 return 1;
841}
842
843int BN_nnmod_pow2(BIGNUM *r, const BIGNUM *a, size_t e) {
844 if (!BN_mod_pow2(r, a, e)) {
845 return 0;
846 }
847
848 // If the returned value was non-negative, we're done.
849 if (BN_is_zero(r) || !r->neg) {
850 return 1;
851 }
852
853 size_t num_words = 1 + (e - 1) / BN_BITS2;
854
855 // Expand |r| to the size of our modulus.
856 if (!bn_wexpand(r, num_words)) {
857 return 0;
858 }
859
860 // Clear the upper words of |r|.
861 OPENSSL_memset(&r->d[r->width], 0, (num_words - r->width) * BN_BYTES);
862
863 // Set parameters of |r|.
864 r->neg = 0;
865 r->width = (int) num_words;
866
867 // Now, invert every word. The idea here is that we want to compute 2^e-|x|,
868 // which is actually equivalent to the twos-complement representation of |x|
869 // in |e| bits, which is -x = ~x + 1.
870 for (int i = 0; i < r->width; i++) {
871 r->d[i] = ~r->d[i];
872 }
873
874 // If our exponent doesn't span the top word, we have to mask the rest.
875 size_t top_word_exponent = e % BN_BITS2;
876 if (top_word_exponent != 0) {
877 r->d[r->width - 1] &= (((BN_ULONG) 1) << top_word_exponent) - 1;
878 }
879
880 // Keep the minimal-width invariant for |BIGNUM|.
881 bn_set_minimal_width(r);
882
883 // Finally, add one, for the reason described above.
884 return BN_add(r, r, BN_value_one());
885}
